  "issue_title": "test: add offline screen understanding validation",
  "issue_body": "Parent: #38\n\n## Problem\n\nMilestone 3 should not be considered complete until screen understanding works offline on representative screens and produces expected summaries, suggestions, and redacted logs.\n\n## Proposed behavior\n\nAdd Milestone 3 offline validation covering screen context and understanding:\n\n- TouchPilot screen\n- Android Settings screen\n- Launcher screen\n- input-field screen\n- weak/limited Accessibility screen if available\n\nValidation should confirm:\n\n- screen context is built locally\n- summary is generated locally\n- suggested actions are generated locally\n- no cloud/backend is required\n- sensitive text remains redacted in logs/traces\n\n## User workflow\n\nA tester should be able to run TouchPilot on emulator or real device, open common screens, ask what TouchPilot sees, and verify that the app responds with local summaries and possible actions.\n\n## Local-first impact\n\nThis proves Milestone 3's core claim: TouchPilot can understand Android screens locally without relying on cloud vision/chat models.\n\n## Safety and security considerations\n\n- Include at least one text-entry or sensitive-looking screen in validation to confirm redaction behavior.\n- Suggested actions should not execute automatically during validation unless explicitly selected.\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n\n- [ ] Add a Milestone 3 offline validation checklist.\n- [ ] Validate TouchPilot screen context.\n- [ ] Validate Android Settings screen context.\n- [ ] Validate launcher screen context.\n- [ ] Validate an input-field screen.\n- [ ] Validate weak/limited Accessibility behavior where practical.\n- [ ] Confirm summaries and suggestions require no cloud/backend.\n- [ ] Confirm logs/traces redact sensitive text where applicable.\n- [ ] Add automated tests where practical and document manual live-test steps.\n\n## References\n\n- Parent issue: #38\n- `docs/LIVE_TESTING.md`\n- `docs/ROADMAP.md` Milestone 3\n",
  "merged_at": "2026-05-25T10:51:27.000Z",
